article.headline: North Texas 66, Middle Tennessee 53
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Calvin Watson scored 21 points, including five 3-pointers, as North Texas defeated Middle Tennessee 66-53 on Thursday night. Watson hit 6-of-11 from the field, including 5-of-10 3-pointers, and four of his six free throws. Michael Sturns added 10 points for the Mean Green (14-6, 5-4 Sun Belt). North Texas' victory snapped a five-game conference winning streak for Middle Tennessee (9-11, 5-5). Tim Blue scored 16 points and had two blocked shots for Middle Tennessee. Kevin Kanaskie scored 14 and Nigel Johnson added 10. North Texas scored 18 points off of Middle Tennessee's 15 turnovers. North Texas led throughout the game, including 27-22 at the half.
